#eNCA #DStv403 Editor's note: Livestream courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA  BLOEMFONTEIN - Former Transnet Board member and Gupta family associate, Iqbal Sharma, is back at the Bloemfontein magistrate's court to apply for bail. Sharma and former Free State agriculture department head, Peter Thabethe, appeared in court on Monday. READ: Gupta associate, Iqbal Sharma bail hearing postponed Thabethe was released on R10,000 bail. They face fraud and money laundering charges worth over R24.9-million linked to a Free State Agricultural department feasibility study.